This is a 'list of objects 1â1000 of the [[New General Catalogue]] (NGC)'. The
astronomical catalogue is composed mainly of star clusters, nebulae, and
galaxies. Other objects in the catalogue can be found in the other subpages of
the list of NGC objects. The constellation information in these tables is from
The Complete New General Catalogue and Index Catalogue of Nebulae and Star
Clusters by J. L. E. Dreyer, {{cite book
 | author=R. W. Sinnott, editor title= The Complete New General Catalogue and
 | Index Catalogue of Nebulae and Star Clusters by J. L. E. Dreyer year=1988
 | publisher=Sky Publishing Corporation and Cambridge University Press isbn=0-933346-51-
 | 4}} which was accessed using the VizieR Service (website: http://vizier.u-strasbg.fr/viz-
 | bin/VizieR). Galaxy morphological types and objects that are members of the
 | Small Magellanic Cloud are identified using the NASA/IPAC Extragalactic
 | Database (website: http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/). The other data of these
 | tables are from the SIMBAD Astronomical Database (website: http://simbad.u-
 | strasbg.fr/simbad/) unless otherwise stated.
